Message.MsgText: DWCT_ExcessiveServiceTime=DWCT0011W: Excessive service time; service time is {0} milliseconds, URL is {1}
Message.Explanation: The processing of the request took longer than the threshold specified by the ExcessiveServiceTimeThresholdInMs cell custom property.
Message.UserResponse: Continue to diagnose why the application, application server, or back end resource took longer than expected.

Message.MsgText: DWCT_Exception2=DWCT0013W: An exception occurred. Exception description: {0} Additional technical data: {1}
Message.Explanation: An exception occurred during processing. The description indicates what the exception is, and additional technical data is optionally provided.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the condition that caused the exception, if known; consult IBM Service for help if the problem persists.

Message.MsgText: DWCT_SARFMConfigErr=DWCT0017E: The value for the property {0} is invalid.
Message.Explanation: The value set for the property is invalid.
Message.UserResponse: Set the property to a valid value and continue.

Message.MsgText: DWCT_UnknownHost=DWCT0020W: Host {0} cannot be resolved to an address.
Message.Explanation: A host name was provided which could not be resolved to an IP address.
Message.UserResponse: Check that the host name is correct, and that it is registered in the DNS and can be resolved.

Message.MsgText: DWCT_MCRPConfigErr=DWCT0010E: Cross cluster routing policy configuration cell or generic cluster {0} is incorrect.
Message.Explanation: The configured cell and/or generic server cluster is not correct.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the configuration in the on demand router and continue.

Message.MsgText: DWCT_SARFMQueueFull=DWCT0019I: A Node-based ARFM queue is full.
Message.Explanation: A Node-based ARFM queue has reached the set queue limit.
Message.UserResponse: Increase the queue limit in the configuration.

Message.MsgText: DWCT_MCRPDefault=DWCT0009I: Cross cluster routing policy has not been defined for the on demand router.
Message.Explanation: No multi-cluster routing policy for the on demand router exists.

Message.MsgText: DWCT_MCRPAppNotFound=DWCT0008E: No application has been deployed on the target cluster.
Message.Explanation: Configured multi-cluster routing policy for an application, but the application has not been deployed on the cluster.
Message.UserResponse: Check your on demand router customization and deploy the appropriate application.

Message.Explanation: An exception occurred during processing. The message may provide additional technical data.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the condition that caused the exception, if known; consult IBM Service for help if the problem persists.

Message.MsgText: DWCT_SARFMQueueing=DWCT0015I: Node-based ARFM added the first request to the queue.
Message.Explanation: Node-based ARFM added the first request to the queue.

Message.MsgText: DWCT_SARFMConfigIgnore=DWCT0016I: Property {0} was changed. This property is ignored when node-based ARFM is enabled
Message.Explanation: Some properties do not apply to node-based ARFM.
